# aidazi — provider credentials for the `headless` harness (OpenAI-compatible APIs).
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in real values. The charter
# references these BY NAME (tooling.<role>.api_key_env / endpoint_env); the engine
# (engine-kit/scheduling/run_loop.py) loads `.env.local` into the environment on
# `--allow-real` runs (an already-exported var always wins). NEVER put a real key
# in the charter or commit `.env.local` — this `.env.example` ships the NAMES only.
#
# Native CLI harnesses (claude_code / codex) need NOTHING here — they authenticate
# via their own CLI config (`claude` / `codex` login). Only headless API providers
# below need keys.

# DeepSeek — the default Review role in the worked examples.
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
# DEEPSEEK_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com/v1   # optional; or set tooling.review.endpoint literally

# Moonshot / Kimi
# MOONSHOT_API_KEY=
# MOONSHOT_BASE_URL=https://api.moonshot.cn/v1

# OpenAI — only if you reach GPT via the headless harness (not via the codex CLI).
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
